{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Base directory for this skill: /Users/wso2/repos/asdlc/remote-worker/plugin/skills/asdlc\n\n# ASDLC\n\nIf you don't know the github repo you are working with, ask for it. All the tasks are based on a github repo.\n\nOnce you have the repo, you can use the gh CLI, to look for the open issues. You can ask the user which one to work on.\n\nYou need to use ASDLC MCP tools commiunicate with the platform.\n\n\n## Developement Flow\n\n- Strictly adhere to whats described in the Github issue of your task.\n- Stay within those boundaries.\n- The issue body has a **Working Directory** section with an absolute path. Before doing anything else, `cd` to that path. Do ALL work inside it — do not create files outside, and do not `cd` elsewhere during the task.\n- Dockerfile must be present in the root of the repo.\n- Once the changes are done, you must build the docker image and verify that it works locally by making api calls if applicable.\n- Then only you can mark it as completed and submit the implementation.\n- Every component must have `workload.yaml` at its root, refer to the github task.\n\nDo **not** run `git` yourself. Do **not** create PRs or branches. Submission triggers commit → push → OpenChoreo build → deploy automatically.\n\n\n## Reporting progress\n\nPeriodically call the `mcp__asdlc__report_progress` MCP tool with:\n- `issueUrl`: the GitHub issue URL for the task\n- `message`: one short sentence\n- `stage`: one of `exploring`, `implementing`, `testing`, `finalizing`\n\nEach call is mirrored as a comment on the GitHub issue.\n\n## Submitting\n\nWhen the component is complete, call `mcp__asdlc__submit_implementation`:\n- `issueUrl`: the GitHub issue URL\n- `summary`: 1–3 sentences describing what was built\n- `port`: the port the service listens on (must match your `workload.yaml`)\n\nThe platform will close the issue with your summary, then automatically commit, push, build, and deploy.\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4f9ade0c-31d4-4ddc-8da4-30caee42e277","uuid":"ffc0ae86-37fb-485f-bc6b-a0349226cfe3","timestamp":"2026-04-26T04:04:59.313Z","isSynthetic":true}
