{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PTwsT5im5gEyd8r7YQXecM","type":"tool_result","content":"title:\tImplement tasks-web React application\nstate:\tOPEN\nauthor:\txlight05\nlabels:\t\ncomments:\t0\nassignees:\t\nprojects:\t\nmilestone:\t\nnumber:\t2\n--\n## Component Constraints\n- **Name:** tasks-web\n- **Type:** web-app\n- **Language/Stack:** TypeScript / React\n- **App Path:** `/tasks-web`\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Provide interactive UI for task creation, viewing, completion toggling, and deletion\n- Communicate with tasks-api REST endpoints for all CRUD operations\n- Display tasks with visual completion status indicators\n- Handle user input validation and error states\n- Implement optimistic UI updates for responsive user experience\n- Serve the application via Nginx with proper SPA routing\n- Support configuration of API URL via environment variables\n- Provide health check endpoint for deployment monitoring\n\n## Key Considerations\n- Use TypeScript with React and Vite for modern development experience\n- Implement proper error handling and user feedback for network failures\n- Ensure responsive design that works across device sizes\n- Use optimistic updates to provide immediate UI feedback\n- Validate task descriptions are non-empty before submission\n- Configure CORS-compatible API requests to backend service\n- Create production-ready Docker image with multi-stage build\n- Set up Nginx to handle SPA client-side routing\n- Support environment-based API URL configuration for different deployment environments\n\n## Project Structure Requirements\nCreate a production-ready project structure in the current directory:\n- package.json with dependencies and scripts\n- tsconfig.json\n- src/ with App component and entry point\n- vite.config.ts\n- Dockerfile (build + nginx for serving)\n\nCreate a `workload.yaml` at the root of your component directory:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: openchoreo.dev/v1alpha1\nmetadata:\n  name: <component-k8s-name>\nspec:\n  autoBuild: true\n  autoDeploy: true\n  endpoints:\n    - name: http\n      port: <port-your-app-listens-on>\n      type: HTTP\n      basePath: /\n      visibility:\n        - external\n```\n\nThe port must match the port your application listens on. Adjust endpoint type, basePath, and add dependencies as needed.\n\nThe platform will handle git commit, push, build, and deploy automatically.\n## OpenAPI Spec\n\n```yaml\nopenapi: 3.0.3\ninfo:\n  title: Tasks Web Application\n  version: 1.0.0\n  description: Frontend web application for todo tasks\npaths:\n  /:\n    get:\n      summary: Serve the web application\n      operationId: serveApp\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: HTML page served successfully\n          content:\n            text/html:\n              schema:\n                type: string\n```\n\n## Agent Instructions\nBuild a React single-page application using TypeScript and Vite that provides a complete task management UI. Create a responsive interface with: (1) a text input and submit button for creating new tasks, (2) a list view displaying all tasks with visual completion indicators (checkboxes/strikethrough), (3) interactive elements to toggle task completion and delete tasks. Use React hooks (useState, useEffect) for state management. Fetch tasks from the tasks-api service on mount using GET /tasks. Implement CRUD operations: POST /tasks for creation, PATCH /tasks/{id} for updating completion status, DELETE /tasks/{id} for deletion. Configure API base URL via VITE_API_URL environment variable (default: http://localhost:9090). Implement optimistic UI updates with rollback on errors, loading states, and user-friendly error messages. Validate non-empty descriptions client-side. Style with clean CSS (centered content, readable fonts, proper spacing). Create a multi-stage Dockerfile: stage 1 builds with npm, stage 2 uses nginx:alpine to serve static files. Configure Nginx for SPA routing (serve index.html for all routes) and add /health endpoint returning 200 OK. Expose port 80.\n\n## Working Directory\nYou are working inside a cloned git repository at your component's source directory.\nCreate all files relative to this directory. Do NOT create files outside it.\n\n## General Constraints\n- Write ALL files in the current working directory (do NOT create files outside it).\n- The component must have a Dockerfile for containerized builds.\n- Implement the full API contract from the task — every endpoint must be functional.\n- Use the dependencies listed to understand what other services this component talks to.\n- The app MUST start without any required environment variables — use sensible hardcoded defaults for all config (JWT secrets, DB paths, API URLs, etc.). Environment variables may override defaults but must never be required.\n- Do NOT stub or mock — write real, working implementations.\n- Do NOT run, start, or execute the application server locally. Only write source files. The platform builds and deploys your code automatically — local execution is unnecessary and will cause port conflicts.\n- If you must run a quick compile check (e.g. `go build`, `tsc --noEmit`), do so without starting a server. Never use `go run`, `npm start`, `node server.js`, or any command that starts a long-running process.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4f9ade0c-31d4-4ddc-8da4-30caee42e277","uuid":"aa0f477a-cbf8-4796-86e1-397cd9e7f424","timestamp":"2026-04-26T04:05:08.884Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"title:\tImplement tasks-web React application\nstate:\tOPEN\nauthor:\txlight05\nlabels:\t\ncomments:\t0\nassignees:\t\nprojects:\t\nmilestone:\t\nnumber:\t2\n--\n## Component Constraints\n- **Name:** tasks-web\n- **Type:** web-app\n- **Language/Stack:** TypeScript / React\n- **App Path:** `/tasks-web`\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Provide interactive UI for task creation, viewing, completion toggling, and deletion\n- Communicate with tasks-api REST endpoints for al